1) How to use:

Basic usage:
Just drag and drop a image onto the PxlTemplateCreator.exe
The template will be saved in this directory named ORIGINALNAME_template_SOMENUMBER.png
On pxls.space you can use this template now BUT you need to add another parameter
to the url - the tw
Just write &tw=THE_NUMBER_FROM_THE_TEMPLATE_NAME after your pxls url with the template and
reload the site

Advanced usage:
Open a commandline in this directory.
In there you can add some parameters to PxlTemplateCreator.exe on call:
-h: Prints the help
-num_transparent_pixels: Number of transparent pixels between each original pixel
-num_solid_pixels: Number of transparent pixels between each transparent pixel
-v: verbose
-out: Ouput filename
-generate_link: Upload the template to imgur and open a pxls.space template link in your
	default webbrowser
e.g. PxlTemplateCreator.exe IMAGEPATH -num_transparent_pixels 2 -v -out MyTemplate
The output filename will be followed by _ORIGINALIMAGEWIDTH.png so no need for you to add
this.
For how to use this on pxls.space see the basic usage section.

